---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Make Your Own Tools | Practical Engineering Calculators"
  description="Learn why Make Your Own Tools exists: practical calculators and generators for homelab, off-grid power, Docker, reverse proxy, and engineering planning."
  canonical="/about/"
>
  <main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:px-8 md:py-16">
    <a href="/" class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-zinc-300 transition hover:border-white/30 hover:bg-white/10">
      <span>←</span>
      <span>Home</span>
    </a>

    <article class="glass-shell-strong rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-9">
      <p class="mb-4 inline-flex rounded-full border border-cyan-300/30 bg-cyan-300/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-cyan-100">
        Independent Tool Studio
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl">About Make Your Own Tools</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-8 text-zinc-300">
        Make Your Own Tools is a small independent website for practical engineering calculators and generators. The goal is simple: turn common planning questions into fast, transparent tools that help people make better decisions before they buy hardware, deploy software, or configure infrastructure.
      </p>

      <section class="mt-8 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/25 p-4">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-cyan-100">Power</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-300">Solar, battery, inverter, and RV off-grid sizing calculators for practical load planning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/25 p-4">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-sky-100">Storage</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-300">NAS and RAID calculators for usable capacity, redundancy, and drive purchase planning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/25 p-4">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-emerald-100">Deployment</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-300">Docker Compose and reverse proxy generators for self-hosted applications and services.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-300">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">How the Site Is Maintained</h2>
        <p>
          The calculators are built as static pages and client-side tools so they load quickly and remain easy to inspect. Form inputs stay in the browser unless a specific feature, such as fetching a public model configuration, clearly needs an external request.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some pages may include product recommendations, donation links, or affiliate links in the future. Those links help support hosting, maintenance, and new calculators without putting a paywall in front of the tools.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
